For a pair of helical gear with right hand shown in Figure 1, the pinion tooth profile Σ1 and gear tooth profile Σ2 are contact surfaces. The profile Σ1 within the coordinate system x1'y1'z1' is expressed as parameters θ1 and u1 as proposed by Litvin,14 which is also being applied here as
(2)r1'={x1'y1'z1'}={rb1cos(θ1+μ1)+u1cosλb1sin(θ1+μ1)-rb1sin(θ1+μ1)+u1cosλb1cos(θ1+μ1)u1sinλb1-p1θ1}
and the unit differential with respect to θ1 and u1 are, respectively
(3)r1θ'=∂r1'∂θ1/|∂r1'∂θ1|={cos(θ1+μ1)-sin(θ1+μ1)0}
(4)r1u'=∂r1'∂u1/|∂r1'∂u1|={cosλb1sin(θ1+μ1)cosλb1cos(θ1+μ1)sinλb1}

The unit normal to the tooth surface Σ1 is given by
(5)n1'=-r1u'×r1θ'|r1u'×r1θ'|={-sinλb1sin(θ1+μ1)-sinλb1cos(θ1+μ1)cosλb1}
where p1 is the screw parameter, μ1=wt1/2rp1-invαt1, wt1 the nominal value of space width on the pitch circle, and αt1 the transverse pressure angle. Also, θ1 is the pressure angle in the cross-section and λb1 the helix angle.

The profile Σ2 within the coordinate system x2'y2'z2' is expressed as parameters θ2 and u2
(6)r2'={x2'y2'z2'}={rb2cos(θ2-ɛ2)+u2cosλb2sin(θ2-ɛ2)-rb2sin(θ2-ɛ2)-u2cosλb2cos(θ2-ɛ2)-u2sinλb2+p2θ2}
(7)r2θ'=∂r2'∂θ2/|∂r2'∂θ2|={-cos(θ2-ɛ2)sin(θ2-ɛ2)0}
(8)r2u'=∂r2'∂u2/|∂r2'∂u2|={cosλb2sin(θ2-ɛ2)-cosλb2cos(θ2-ɛ2)-sinλb2}
(9)n2'=-r2u'×r2θ'|r2u'×r2θ'|={sinλb2sin(θ2-ɛ2)-sinλb2cos(θ2-ɛ2)cosλb2}

Within the half cylinder in the vicinity of contact point P(xi, yi, zi) in the tooth contact area Γ, as shown in Figure 3, the local coordinate ξiηiζi is used to define the deformation and stress around the vicinity of the point P(xi, yi, zi) where ξi-axis is perpendicular to the z-axis; ηi-axis is normal to the surface at the point and ζi-axis is orthogonal to both ξi and ηi. Borrowing from the theory proposed by Johnson,16 the deformation uξi, vηi and wζi at generic point A(ξ,η,ζ) caused by contact load pi can be expressed as
(19)uξi=pi4πG{ξζρi3-(1-2v)ξρi(ρi+ζ)}
(20)vηi=pi4πG{ηζρi3-(1-2v)ηρi(ρi+ζ)}
(21)wζi=pi4πG{ζ2ρi3+2(1-v)ρi}
where G is the shear modulus, v the Poisson ratio, and ρi=ξ2+η2+ζ2. The corresponding stress σξi, σηi, σζi, τξηi, τξζi and τηζi at a generic point A caused by contact load pi are
(22)σξi=pi2π{(1-2v)ri2[(1-ζρi)ξ2-η2ri2+ζη2ρi3]-3ζξ2ρi5}
(23)σηi=pi2π{(1-2v)ri2[(1-ζρi)η2-ξ2ri2+ζξ2ρi3]-3ζη2ρi5}
(24)σζi=-3pi2πζ3ρi5
where ri=ξ2+η2
Figure 3.
Small tooth area in the vicinity of the contact load pi.
